Author:
Vol / Page: 10
Edition:
Quote: New Zealand's wet alpine areas are home to what is thought to be the world's smallest conifer, the pygmy pine, Lepidothamnus laxifolius. This "pine" doesn't even make it as a shrub, let alone a forest specimen, but spreads in a cushion.
